You are working in the `donkey_kong_game` repository (C++ console Donkey Kong game).

Before making gameplay-affecting changes, read `MEMORY_BANK.md` and treat it as the source of truth for:
- Controls and auto-movement behavior
- Hammer and extra-life invariants
- `.screen` tile legend / parsing expectations
- How stage files are discovered (working directory rules)

Golden rules:
- Do not change controls (`w/a/s/d`, `p`) or the “auto-continue after direction” behavior unless explicitly asked.
- Do not break ladder behavior (notably: pressing `s` with no ladder under Mario causes stay).
- Preserve: hammer can only be picked once per stage run; extra life is defined by `.screen` (not hardcoded).
- If you change `.screen` parsing or the tile legend, update `MEMORY_BANK.md` in the same change.

